As a superuser, you can amend family portal interactions by creating a new Family Portal Role. Here's how:

  1. Go to Menu > Administration > Roles
  2. Click the blue '+' and select 'Family Member Role'
  3. Give the role a title
  4. Click the 3 dots next to 'interactions'
  5. Specify which interactions can be seen (view only) or not seen (no access)
  6. Click 'Save'

Then, assign this new role to the family member in their profile.


Sources:
Setting up Roles
Family Portal - Roles

The care plan might appear blacked out due to accidental archiving. To fix this:

  1. Go to the resident's Care Plan.
  2. Click the eye icon at the top of the page to view archived elements.
  3. Look for archived sections with an eye icon next to them.
  4. Click the eye icon next to the archived element to un-archive it.

If a whole folder is archived, you can unarchive it by:

  1. Clicking the + symbol in the Care Plan tab.
  2. Selecting "Folder" and choosing the archived folder's title.
  3. Clicking "Create" to make it reappear.

If issues persist, please ask for human support.

How to view an Archived Care / Support Plan and un-archive if needed

Good afternoon Paul,

To add future pay rates for care staff, you can follow these steps:

  1. Navigate to Payment Groups:
    • Go to Finance > Payments > Payment Groups.
    • Use the "Copy existing group" button to duplicate an existing group, creating a new group with 'Copy of...' at the start of its name.
  2. Configure the New Group:
    • In the pop-up window, select the group you want to copy from the ‘Existing group’ menu.
    • Choose to supersede client/carer assignments to automatically replace the default payment group of any carers assigned to the original group with the newly copied group.
  3. Set Rates to Manual:
    • Use the Set existing rate(s) to “Manual” option to change any automatic rates in the original group to manual, allowing rates to be applied manually to appointments.
  4. Save and Adjust Settings:
    • Click Save to finalize the new group, retaining any settings and descriptions from the original group.
    • Update details by clicking the group name to open General Settings, adjust the Group Name, and make other necessary changes, then Save.
  5. Assign Groups to Carers:
    • Assign carers or clients to specific invoice/payment groups to give them access to the rates within that group.

These steps will help you set up future pay rates effectively.

The two articles below do explain how to set up rates within the system. Updating rates can be different from company to company depending on the needs, so it doesn't have an exact guide for this.

When rates are being changed in the middle of a payment/invoice period, you would need to make sure you have two of each rate, you would then make one manual and the other automatic depending upon which date range you're confirming + updating within the confirm appointments pages.

For example, if you were running a timesheet from the 1st to the 30th and your new rates started on the 15th, you would confirm all the appointments up till the 15th, go into your finance rates, switch the current rate to 'Manual' then create a new rate going forward. To finish you would need to go into confirm appointments and autocorrect all the appointments from the 15th up until the current date.

If you go into your rates and create your new rate exactly the same as the prior rate, once done, go into your old rate and change it so that it applies manually instead of automatically

From here go into your confirm appointments page and confirm your appointments up until the 5th which will lock the rates in up until your rate change period. From the 5th onward, auto correct your finance rates, which will move them to the new rate as it will apply the most applicable rate.
